  "text": "We proposed a multiscale approach allowing the advection of different frequency bands. While the choice of the number of advected frequency bands can remain a user-defined choice, this can lead to an undesired linear interpolation in certain cases. For example, if BRDF A only contains high frequencies and BRDF B only contains low frequencies, the multiscale approach will advect the high frequencies of BRDF A toward a frequency band with zero energy in the BRDF B, hence fading out the high frequency band. This is illustrated in Fig.10 . This behavior becomes more likely as we increase the number of frequency bands. The use of different frequency decompositions such as Empirical Mode Decomposition or based on local extrema [CITATION_1] ] remains a challenge for scattered data, but could provide a better multiscale representation.",
